19. limite aeto: to Tacitus and his readers limes in this pas- sage meant the fortified boundary line separating Roman from German territory. Vespasian (69—79) took steps to secure Roman possession of the Agyri Decumates by extending a military road east from Strassburg and planting castella in the valley of the Neokar. The real credit for achieving permanent extension of the Roman frontier north and east of the Middle thne belongs to Domitian. As a result of his campaign against the Chatti, 83 A.D., this emperor began a great system of fortifications, which, strengthened and extended by Trajan, Hadrian, and An- toninus Pius, ultimately stretched from Honningen, situated on the Rhine not far above Bonn, to Hienheim on the Danube, near Regensburg.
